# Caddy reverse proxy: automatic HTTPS via Let's Encrypt.
# DOMAIN comes from the environment (set in deploy/.env).
#
# BLOCKER overcome: the MCP server itself only speaks plain HTTP, but
# claude.ai / Claude Desktop refuse to connect to a remote MCP server over
# HTTP. Caddy sits in front, gets a free cert for DOMAIN automatically (needs
# a real DNS name, e.g. via DuckDNS, and port 80 open for the ACME challenge),
# and forwards the now-HTTPS traffic to the mcp container on 8080.

{$DOMAIN} {
	reverse_proxy mcp:8080
}
